status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"drnt0","text":"Plate ~3.6x106 Lenti-X HEK293T cells (Takara) in 10 cm dish in 10 mL standard DMEM. Cells should be ~80% confluent at the time of transfection. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2m57h","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"fesev","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"15jtc","text":"NOTE: Only low passage cells should be used.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"49fis","text":"Next day, remove 5 mL medium and replenish with fresh medium.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1k0ic","text":"Warm up reduced serum medium e.g. Opti-MEM (Gibco) and transfection reagent to room temperature (RT). This protocol was performed with Lipofectamine 3000 transfection reagent (Thermo).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"acrb6","text":"Add 24 µL Lipofectamine 3000 to 600 µL Opti-MEM, mix by vortexing and incubate 5 min at RT.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cqmec","text":"In another tube, mix 6 µg plasmid containing gene of interest, 5 µg packaging plasmid psPAX2 ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8aure","text":"(RRID:Addgene_12260), 1 µg envelope plasmid pMD2.G (RRID:Addgene_12259) and 24 µL P3000 reagent (provided by manufacturer along with Lipofectamine 3000 reagent) in 600 µL Opti-MEM, mix by vortexing and incubate 5 min at RT.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"eo0hn","text":"Mix contents of both tubes and incubate for 15 min at RT.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fthii","text":"2 days later, collect virus-containing medium and centrifuge for 5 min at 1,000 x g.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"3bhtv","text":"Collect supernatant in a fresh tube and proceed with concentration.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bv0t1","text":"Next day, centrifuge for 45 min at 1,500 x g at 4 °C followed by gently aspirating supernatant.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5a74p","text":"Resuspend viral pellet in 100 - 1000 µL PBS, aliquot and store at -80 °C until use.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7vrg5","text":"Add Lenti-X concentrator (Takara) to clarified virus-containing medium at 1:4 dilution and mix well by gently inverting tube.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
